<p>Savannah's hot-humid climate demands robust HVAC systems capable of handling both high temperatures and moisture control. The optimal HVAC system for Savannah homes should have a minimum SEER rating of 16, with high-efficiency units rated at 18-20 SEER providing the best long-term value. Heat pumps are particularly effective in Savannah's mild winter climate, offering both heating and cooling efficiency while working synergistically with solar panel systems.</p>

