<p>Newer developments in Pooler and Richmond Hill offer ideal conditions for solar installations with modern roof designs and fewer restrictions. The Southside and Midtown areas feature a mix of housing styles, with many ranch-style homes providing excellent south-facing roof exposure for solar panels. Islands communities like Whitemarsh Island and Wilmington Island benefit from excellent solar exposure but may require additional consideration for salt air corrosion protection. Regardless of neighborhood, most Savannah homes can benefit from solar installations, with professional site assessments determining optimal system design and placement.</p>

